Business Brief -- Burr-Brown Corp.:
   Pretax Charge to Be Posted,
   Causing a 4th-Quarter Loss
In the year-earlier fourth quarter, Burr-Brown earned
$672,000, or seven cents a share, on sales of $48.3 million.
For all of 1990, the company posted net income of $4.3
million, or 44 cents a share, on sales of $177 million.
   Among the elements of the restructuring program, which was
first outlined last November, are: slimming down domestic
operations; reorganizing the European sales and distribution
systems; quitting a military electronics business; and
reducing manufacturing capacity.